<paragraph id="8BCD94236F06FFEB0BFCFBCFFE75FB07" blockId="120.[189,1399,1038,1276]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F06FFEB0BFCFBCFFE1EFBD4" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,430,1038,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficrus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F06FFEB0BFCFBCFFE1EFBD4" box="[189,430,1038,1064]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Mesoconius ruficrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F06FFEB0AF8FBCFFDA6FBD5" box="[441,534,1039,1065]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to the sympatric 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F06FFEB0824FBCFFBADFBD4" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[869,1053,1038,1064]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadritheca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F06FFEB0824FBCFFBADFBD4" box="[869,1053,1038,1064]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">M. quadritheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F06FFEB0F66FBCFFB34FBD5" box="[1063,1156,1039,1065]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and to the Bolivian species 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F06FFEB0A5EFBF2FE3BFBB7" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[287,395,1074,1099]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigra" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F06FFEB0A5EFBF2FE3BFBB7" box="[287,395,1074,1099]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">M. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F06FFEB0AD9FBF2FE48FBB0" box="[408,504,1074,1100]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
These species share the limited constriction at the abdominal base, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F06FFEB0BFCFB95FEF2FB93" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[189,322,1109,1135]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficrus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F06FFEB0BFCFB95FEF2FB93" box="[189,322,1109,1135]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">M. ruficrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F06FFEB0A0CFB95FE1BFB93" box="[333,427,1109,1135]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has red legs, in marked contrast to the black legs of the other two species. An apparent undescribed fourth species in this group, characterized by basally red and distally black femora, a bicoloured pleuron (black dorsally and pale ventrally) and broad black wings is known only from a photograph of a female (
<figureCitation id="134988A66F06FFEB0AA0FB7EFDFAFB24" box="[481,586,1214,1240]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="119.[189,232,1917,1943]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,486,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@119.[189,1398,486,1886]" captionTargetPageId="119" captionText="Fig. 49. A–E. Mesoconius ruficrus sp. nov. A. Living ♀. B. Posterior part of thorax, lateral view. C. Head. D. Holotype, ♀, MUSM, dorsal view showing wing. E. Spermathecae and associated structures. — F. Undescribed species of Mesoconius Enderlein, 1922 from Wayqecha Biological Station, Peru." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3402001/files/figure.png" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Fig. 49F</figureCitation>
), taken at the same time and place where the 
<typeStatus id="54C92A816F06FFEB0F25FB7EFB7BFB24" box="[1124,1227,1214,1240]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C72EFA06F06FFEB0FB2FB7FFAC6FB24" authority="Marshall, 2019" authorityName="Marshall" authorityYear="2019" box="[1267,1398,1214,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Mesoconius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficrus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B90648316F06FFEB0FB2FB7FFAC6FB24" box="[1267,1398,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">M. ruficrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A235F54A6F06FFEB0BFCFB22FEA8FB00" box="[189,280,1250,1276]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
was collected.
</paragraph>
